    <h1>Best practice: Neckermann</h1><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_cancellation_and_returns">Cancellation and returns</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This best practice deals with cancellations and returns for the market Neckermann.</p>
</div>
<h3 id="_partial_cancellation" class="discrete">Partial cancellation</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Situation:</strong> The order has not been shipped yet. The order contains several positions and one position is to be cancelled. The other positions are to be shipped.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Procedure:</strong> Set the position which is to be cancelled to 0 and select the reason for the cancellation. Select <strong>Item not in stock</strong> if the item cannot be shipped. Select <strong>Customer cancellation</strong> if the customer wishes to cancel the item. Ship the other positions. To do so, book the outgoing items.</p>
</div>
<h3 id="_cancellation" class="discrete">Cancellation</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Situation:</strong> The order has not been shipped yet. All positions are to be cancelled.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Procedure:</strong> If you cancelled the order, set it to <strong>status [8]</strong>. If the customer cancelled the order, set it to <strong>status [8.1]</strong>.</p>
</div>
